  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "Native System V IPC message queues in Node.js with bindings and an easy to use abstraction. [System V message queues](http://linux.die.net/man/7/svipc) are more widely implemented on UNIX systems than [POSIX message queues](http://linux.die.net/man/7/mq_overview), and are supported on both Linux and OS X.",
    "context": "Native System V IPC message queues in Node.js with bindings and an easy to use abstraction. [System V message queues](http://linux.die.net/man/7/svipc) are more widely implemented on UNIX systems than [POSIX message queues](http://linux.die.net/man/7/mq_overview), and are supported on both Linux and OS X.\n\nThese are FIFO queues. New messages are pushed to the end and old messages are popped off first.",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
